Who they are:
Inexperienced attackers who use pre-written tools and scripts without understanding how they work.

Motivation:

Fun or curiosity

Gaining attention

Proving skills (often unsuccessfully)

Skills Level: Low

Typical Attacks:

Website defacement

Basic DDoS attacks

Running automated scanners (Nmap, Metasploit)

Real-world Example:

Defacing small websites using tools downloaded from GitHub

ğŸ“Œ Threat level: Low, but still dangerous due to volume.

